  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN172-kilavi">tōḻi taḷaimakaḷai <app><lem>yiṭattuyttut</lem><rdg wit="#C7 #C9v #RK"/>vantu</app> taḷaimakaṉai <app><lem>etirppaṭṭu</lem><rdg wit="#RK">/</rdg></app> varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante after having sent HER to the [meeting] place faced HIM [and] urged for marriage.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN172">
        <l>vāraṇa muraṟṟu nīrtikaḻ cilampiṟ</l>
        <l>piracamoṭu viraii vayaṅkuveḷ ḷaruvi</l>
        <l>yiṉṉicai yimiḻiyaṅ kaṭuppa vimmeṉak</l>
        <l>kaṉmukai viṭarakañ cilampa vīḻuṅ</l>
        <l>kāmpu talai maṇanta vōṅkumalaic cāra</l>
        <l>lirumpuvaṭit taṉṉa karuṅkaik kāṉavaṉ</l>
        <l>virimalar marāam poruntik kōṟerintu</l>
        <l>varinutal yāṉai yaruniṟat taḻutti</l>
        <l>yikalaṭu muṉpiṉ veṇkōṭu koṇṭutaṉ</l>
        <l>putalvēy kurampaip pulara <supplied>vū</supplied>ṉṟi</l>
        <l>muṉṟi ṉīṭiya muḻavuṟaḻ palaviṟ</l>
        <l>piḻimaki ḻuvakaiyaṉ kiḷaiyoṭu kaliciṟantu</l>
        <l>cānta ñekiḻiyi ṉūṉpuḻuk kayaruṅ</l>
        <l>kuṉṟa nāṭanī yaṉpilai yākuta</l>
        <l>laṟiyē ṉaṟuraṉaḵ taṟintaṉe ṉāyi</l>
        <l>ṉa<supplied>ṇi</supplied>yiḻai yuṇka ṇāyitaḻk kuṟumakaṇ</l>
        <l>maṇiyēr māṇalañ citaiyap</l>
        <l>pōkunar pacalai yā<supplied>yi</supplied>ṉṟu maṉṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O man from a land of hills, (14ab)</l>
        <l>where on the slope of the high mountain that is entangled with bamboo, (5)</l>
        <l>when fowls shriek [and] glowing white waterfalls</l>
        <l>mixed with honey combs descend from the water-glittering mountain side,</l>
        <l>so that they resound inside the caves [and] clefts in the stones,</l>
        <l>humming like sweet-sounding droning instruments, (1-4)</l>
        <l>the forest man with hands black as if made of iron (5)</l>
        <l>approaches the wide-blossomed Kadamba, tests [its] stems [for arrows] (6)</l>
        <l>plunges [them] into the vital spot difficult [to hit] of the elephant with lined forehead, (7)</l>
        <l>takes the white tusks of hostile strength to kill, (8)</l>
        <l>leans [them] against his bush-covered hut in order to dry, (9)</l>
        <l>[then] in his joy rejoicing in toddy [made] from jack fruits that resemble</l>
        <l>elongated drums in the front-yard along with [his] relatives, with enormous bustle, (11f.)</l>
        <l>engages in [preparing] boiled food with meat with a firebrand of sandal, (13)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">that you would be without love (14cd)</l>
        <l>I did not know. If I had known of that failing strength, (15)</l>
        <l>would there really have been pallor on account of someone who is going [away now], (18)</l>
        <l>for [her] sapphire-like glorious beauty to be wasted, (17)</l>
        <l>on the little woman with adorning jewels, kajal eyes [and] choice lashes? (16)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
